        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Trump unlikely to ever commit ground US forces to Iran, expert says Middle East Issued on: 05/03/2026 - 21:26 Share Top US officials, including the Defense Secretary, have said that sending US troops into Iran could not be ruled out. FRANCE 24's Mark Owen speaks with Daniel Schneiderman, Director of Global Policy Programs at Penn Washington. He says that US President Donald Trump is unlikely to ever commit ground forces to Iran because \"there's a degree of ability to deny that the US is involved in a long-standing war during an air campaign\". Video by: Monte FRANCIS / Mark OWEN Keywords for this article Iran Israel Middle East Kurds Iraq Syria Turkey US claims Iran's missile capabilities 'severely degraded' 05/03/2026 Middle East Qatar says 14 ballistic missiles and 4 drones intercepted 05/03/2026 Middle East US war on Iran has no Plan B, warns Scott Lucas: 'Trump just wants to kill people and blow stuff up' 05/03/2026 Middle East Lebanon: Tens of thousands of residents displaced ahead of fresh Israeli strikes 05/03/2026 Middle East Israel's Lebanon offensive 'may ultimately legitimise Hezbollah, reinforce narrative of resistance' 05/03/2026 Middle East Azerbaijan: Drone strike on an airport and near a school 05/03/2026 Middle East 'No to Israel': US veteran violently dragged from Senate during protest 05/03/2026 Americas US Senate blocks resolution that would stop attacks in Iran 05/03/2026 Americas Amid relentless US and Israeli strikes, Iran seeks to 'wreak havoc across the region' 05/03/2026 Middle East"
