        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. US claims Iran's missile capabilities 'severely degraded' Middle East Issued on: 05/03/2026 - 21:22 Share Washington claims it has severely degraded Iran's missile capabilities, but as the war continues and Iran retaliates, it seems that the country's military capabilities are far from being extinguished. FRANCE 24's Luke Shrago reports. Video by: Luke SHRAGO Keywords for this article Iran Israel Trump unlikely to ever commit ground US forces to Iran, expert says 05/03/2026 Middle East Qatar says 14 ballistic missiles and 4 drones intercepted 05/03/2026 Middle East US war on Iran has no Plan B, warns Scott Lucas: 'Trump just wants to kill people and blow stuff up' 05/03/2026 Middle East Lebanon: Tens of thousands of residents displaced ahead of fresh Israeli strikes 05/03/2026 Middle East Israel's Lebanon offensive 'may ultimately legitimise Hezbollah, reinforce narrative of resistance' 05/03/2026 Middle East Azerbaijan: Drone strike on an airport and near a school 05/03/2026 Middle East 'No to Israel': US veteran violently dragged from Senate during protest 05/03/2026 Americas US Senate blocks resolution that would stop attacks in Iran 05/03/2026 Americas Amid relentless US and Israeli strikes, Iran seeks to 'wreak havoc across the region' 05/03/2026 Middle East"
